summary:
The Security Council,

Recalling previous resolutions on Iraq and the President's statement of 26 February 2010,
welcoming Iraq's progress on non-proliferation and disarmament commitments,
Recognizing Iraq's goal of achieving international standing equal to that prior to resolution 661,

Adopted resolution 1957 (2010), 

1. Terminating weapons of mass destruction, missile, and civil nuclear-related measures imposed by paragraphs 8, 9, 10, 12, and 13 of resolution 687 (1991) and paragraph 3 (f) of resolution 707 (1991);

2. Urging Iraq to ratify the Additional Protocol to the Comprehensive Safeguards Agreement and the Comprehensive Nuclear-Test-Ban Treaty as soon as possible;

3. Deciding to review in one year Iraq's progress on ratifying the Additional Protocol and meeting Chemical Weapons Convention obligations, and requesting the Secretary-General to report to the Council;

4. Deciding to remain actively seized of the matter.
